{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":782,"text":"Imagine you're in Rome,"},{"time":2711,"text":"and you've made your way\nto the Vatican Museums."},{"time":6301,"text":"And you've been shuffling\ndown long corridors,"},{"time":9568,"text":"past statues, frescoes,\nlots and lots of stuff."},{"time":14380,"text":"You're heading towards the Sistine Chapel."},{"time":16749,"text":"At last -- a long corridor,\na stair and a door."},{"time":22149,"text":"You're at the threshold\nof the Sistine Chapel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25171,"text":"So what are you expecting?"},{"time":26959,"text":"Soaring domes? Choirs of angels?"},{"time":29507,"text":"We don't really have any of that there."},{"time":32109,"text":"Instead, you may ask yourself,\nwhat do we have?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":36022,"text":"Well, curtains up on the Sistine Chapel."},{"time":38670,"text":"And I mean literally, you're surrounded\nby painted curtains,"},{"time":41649,"text":"the original decoration of this chapel."},{"time":44088,"text":"Churches used tapestries not just\nto keep out cold during long masses,"},{"time":48656,"text":"but as a way to represent\nthe great theater of life."},{"time":52631,"text":"The human drama in which each one of us\nplays a part is a great story,"},{"time":57786,"text":"a story that encompasses the whole world"},{"time":60619,"text":"and that came to unfold\nin the three stages"},{"time":63708,"text":"of the painting in the Sistine Chapel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66382,"text":"Now, this building started out\nas a space for a small group"},{"time":69767,"text":"of wealthy, educated Christian priests."},{"time":72528,"text":"They prayed there.\nThey elected their pope there."},{"time":75229,"text":"Five hundred years ago,"},{"time":76405,"text":"it was the ultimate\necclesiastical man cave."},{"time":79548,"text":"So, you may ask, how can it be\nthat today it attracts and delights"},{"time":85443,"text":"five million people a year,"},{"time":88133,"text":"from all different backgrounds?"},{"time":90396,"text":"Because in that compressed space,\nthere was a creative explosion,"},{"time":94956,"text":"ignited by the electric excitement\nof new geopolitical frontiers,"},{"time":99812,"text":"which set on fire the ancient\nmissionary tradition of the Church"},{"time":104131,"text":"and produced one of the greatest\nworks of art in history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":108064,"text":"Now, this development took place\nas a great evolution,"},{"time":112602,"text":"moving from the beginning of a few elite,"},{"time":115361,"text":"and eventually able to speak\nto audiences of people"},{"time":118816,"text":"that come from all over the world."},{"time":121222,"text":"This evolution took place in three stages,"},{"time":124000,"text":"each one linked\nto a historical circumstance."},{"time":127135,"text":"The first one was rather limited in scope."},{"time":129190,"text":"It reflected the rather\nparochial perspective."},{"time":132096,"text":"The second one took place after\nworldviews were dramatically altered"},{"time":136374,"text":"after Columbus's historical voyage;"},{"time":139089,"text":"and the third,"},{"time":140520,"text":"when the Age of Discovery\nwas well under way"},{"time":143520,"text":"and the Church rose to the challenge"},{"time":146053,"text":"of going global."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148330,"text":"The original decoration of this church\nreflected a smaller world."},{"time":152366,"text":"There were busy scenes"},{"time":153704,"text":"that told the stories of the lives\nof Jesus and Moses,"},{"time":157585,"text":"reflecting the development\nof the Jewish and Christian people."},{"time":161646,"text":"The man who commissioned this,\nPope Sixtus IV,"},{"time":164007,"text":"assembled a dream team of Florentine art,"},{"time":167350,"text":"including men like Sandro Botticelli"},{"time":170273,"text":"and the man who would become\nMichelangelo's future painting teacher,"},{"time":173874,"text":"Ghirlandaio."},{"time":175436,"text":"These men, they blanketed the walls\nwith a frieze of pure color,"},{"time":180805,"text":"and in these stories you'll notice\nfamiliar landscapes,"},{"time":184130,"text":"the artists using Roman monuments\nor a Tuscan landscape"},{"time":188020,"text":"to render a faraway story,\nsomething much more familiar."},{"time":191472,"text":"With the addition of images\nof the Pope's friends and family,"},{"time":195141,"text":"this was a perfect decoration\nfor a small court"},{"time":197998,"text":"limited to the European continent."},{"time":200244,"text":"But in 1492, the New World was discovered,"},{"time":205138,"text":"horizons were expanding,"},{"time":207106,"text":"and this little 133 by 46-foot\nmicrocosm had to expand as well."},{"time":213486,"text":"And it did,"},{"time":214830,"text":"thanks to a creative genius,"},{"time":216806,"text":"a visionary and an awesome story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220208,"text":"Now, the creative genius\nwas Michelangelo Buonarroti,"},{"time":222781,"text":"33 years old when he was tapped\nto decorate 12,000 square feet of ceiling,"},{"time":227195,"text":"and the deck was stacked against him --"},{"time":229100,"text":"he had trained in painting\nbut had left to pursue sculpture."},{"time":232020,"text":"There were angry patrons in Florence\nbecause he had left a stack"},{"time":235502,"text":"of incomplete commissions,"},{"time":237200,"text":"lured to Rome by the prospect\nof a great sculptural project,"},{"time":240887,"text":"and that project had fallen through."},{"time":243492,"text":"And he had been left with a commission\nto paint 12 apostles"},{"time":246645,"text":"against a decorative background\nin the Sistine Chapel ceiling,"},{"time":249590,"text":"which would look like\nevery other ceiling in Italy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253615,"text":"But genius rose to the challenge."},{"time":255470,"text":"In an age when a man dared\nto sail across the Atlantic Ocean,"},{"time":258992,"text":"Michelangelo dared to chart\nnew artistic waters."},{"time":263027,"text":"He, too, would tell a story --"},{"time":265287,"text":"no Apostles -- but a story\nof great beginnings,"},{"time":268843,"text":"the story of Genesis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271087,"text":"Not really an easy sell,\nstories on a ceiling."},{"time":274042,"text":"How would you be able to read\na busy scene from 62 feet below?"},{"time":278874,"text":"The painting technique that had been\nhanded on for 200 years"},{"time":281753,"text":"in Florentine studios was not equipped\nfor this kind of a narrative."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285694,"text":"But Michelangelo wasn't really a painter,"},{"time":288686,"text":"and so he played to his strengths."},{"time":290994,"text":"Instead of being accustomed\nto filling space with busyness,"},{"time":294500,"text":"he took a hammer and chisel\nand hacked away at a piece of marble"},{"time":298323,"text":"to reveal the figure within."},{"time":300777,"text":"Michelangelo was an essentialist;"},{"time":302969,"text":"he would tell his story\nin massive, dynamic bodies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":307379,"text":"This plan was embraced\nby the larger-than-life Pope Julius II,"},{"time":312170,"text":"a man who was unafraid\nof Michelangelo's brazen genius."},{"time":315815,"text":"He was nephew to Pope Sixtus IV,"},{"time":317721,"text":"and he had been steeped in art\nfor 30 years and he knew its power."},{"time":321852,"text":"And history has handed down the moniker\nof the Warrior Pope,"},{"time":324940,"text":"but this man's legacy to the Vatican --\nit wasn't fortresses and artillery,"},{"time":328754,"text":"it was art."},{"time":330094,"text":"He left us the Raphael Rooms,\nthe Sistine Chapel."},{"time":332697,"text":"He left St. Peter's Basilica"},{"time":334366,"text":"as well as an extraordinary collection\nof Greco-Roman sculptures --"},{"time":340093,"text":"decidedly un-Christian works\nthat would become the seedbed"},{"time":344257,"text":"of the world's first modern museum,\nthe Vatican Museums."},{"time":348847,"text":"Julius was a man"},{"time":350295,"text":"who envisioned a Vatican\nthat would be eternally relevant"},{"time":354103,"text":"through grandeur and through beauty,"},{"time":356216,"text":"and he was right."},{"time":357612,"text":"The encounter between these two giants,\nMichelangelo and Julius II,"},{"time":362624,"text":"that's what gave us the Sistine Chapel."},{"time":365641,"text":"Michelangelo was so committed\nto this project,"},{"time":368452,"text":"that he succeeded in getting the job done\nin three and a half years,"},{"time":372859,"text":"using a skeleton crew and spending\nmost of the time, hours on end,"},{"time":377152,"text":"reaching up above his head\nto paint the stories on the ceiling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381424,"text":"So let's look at this ceiling"},{"time":383498,"text":"and see storytelling gone global."},{"time":386353,"text":"No more familiar artistic references\nto the world around you."},{"time":390789,"text":"There's just space\nand structure and energy;"},{"time":395456,"text":"a monumental painted framework\nwhich opens onto nine panels,"},{"time":400077,"text":"more driven by sculptural form\nthan painterly color."},{"time":404034,"text":"And we stand in the far end\nby the entrance,"},{"time":407835,"text":"far from the altar and from the gated\nenclosure intended for the clergy"},{"time":411965,"text":"and we peer into the distance,\nlooking for a beginning."},{"time":417236,"text":"And whether in scientific inquiry\nor in biblical tradition,"},{"time":421276,"text":"we think in terms of a primal spark."},{"time":424620,"text":"Michelangelo gave us an initial energy"},{"time":426777,"text":"when he gave us the separation\nof light and dark,"},{"time":429542,"text":"a churning figure blurry in the distance,"},{"time":432955,"text":"compressed into a tight space."},{"time":435463,"text":"The next figure looms larger,"},{"time":437816,"text":"and you see a figure hurtling\nfrom one side to the next."},{"time":441267,"text":"He leaves in his wake\nthe sun, the moon, vegetation."},{"time":446277,"text":"Michelangelo didn't focus\non the stuff that was being created,"},{"time":450308,"text":"unlike all the other artists."},{"time":452376,"text":"He focused on the act of creation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455743,"text":"And then the movement stops,\nlike a caesura in poetry"},{"time":460141,"text":"and the creator hovers."},{"time":461417,"text":"So what's he doing?"},{"time":462720,"text":"Is he creating land? Is he creating sea?"},{"time":465599,"text":"Or is he looking back over his handiwork,\nthe universe and his treasures,"},{"time":470314,"text":"just like Michelangelo must have,"},{"time":472069,"text":"looking back over his work in the ceiling"},{"time":474690,"text":"and proclaiming, \"It is good.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":478388,"text":"So now the scene is set,"},{"time":480517,"text":"and you get to the culmination\nof creation, which is man."},{"time":484219,"text":"Adam leaps to the eye, a light figure\nagainst a dark background."},{"time":488573,"text":"But looking closer,"},{"time":490355,"text":"that leg is pretty languid on the ground,"},{"time":493031,"text":"the arm is heavy on the knee."},{"time":495345,"text":"Adam lacks that interior spark"},{"time":499046,"text":"that will impel him to greatness."},{"time":501358,"text":"That spark is about to be conferred\nby the creator in that finger,"},{"time":506147,"text":"which is one millimeter\nfrom the hand of Adam."},{"time":508842,"text":"It puts us at the edge of our seats,"},{"time":510811,"text":"because we're one moment\nfrom that contact,"},{"time":513850,"text":"through which that man\nwill discover his purpose,"},{"time":516775,"text":"leap up and take his place\nat the pinnacle of creation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519783,"text":"And then Michelangelo threw a curveball."},{"time":523068,"text":"Who is in that other arm?"},{"time":525531,"text":"Eve, first woman."},{"time":527251,"text":"No, she's not an afterthought.\nShe's part of the plan."},{"time":530184,"text":"She's always been in his mind."},{"time":532681,"text":"Look at her, so intimate with God\nthat her hand curls around his arm."},{"time":537329,"text":"And for me, an American art historian\nfrom the 21st century,"},{"time":542761,"text":"this was the moment\nthat the painting spoke to me."},{"time":545637,"text":"Because I realized that this\nrepresentation of the human drama"},{"time":549009,"text":"was always about men and women --"},{"time":551946,"text":"so much so, that the dead center,\nthe heart of the ceiling,"},{"time":555760,"text":"is the creation of woman, not Adam."},{"time":558198,"text":"And the fact is, that when you see them\ntogether in the Garden of Eden,"},{"time":562146,"text":"they fall together"},{"time":563707,"text":"and together their proud posture\nturns into folded shame."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568647,"text":"You are at critical juncture\nnow in the ceiling."},{"time":571340,"text":"You are exactly at the point\nwhere you and I can go"},{"time":574447,"text":"no further into the church."},{"time":575926,"text":"The gated enclosure keeps us\nout of the inner sanctum,"},{"time":579306,"text":"and we are cast out\nmuch like Adam and Eve."},{"time":581843,"text":"The remaining scenes in the ceiling,"},{"time":583623,"text":"they mirror the crowded chaos\nof the world around us."},{"time":586491,"text":"You have Noah and his Ark and the flood."},{"time":588739,"text":"You have Noah. He's making a sacrifice\nand a covenant with God."},{"time":592353,"text":"Maybe he's the savior."},{"time":594031,"text":"Oh, but no, Noah is the one\nwho grew grapes, invented wine,"},{"time":597787,"text":"got drunk and passed out\nnaked in his barn."},{"time":600385,"text":"It is a curious way to design the ceiling,"},{"time":602783,"text":"now starting out with God creating life,"},{"time":604731,"text":"ending up with some guy\nblind drunk in a barn."},{"time":607250,"text":"And so, compared with Adam,"},{"time":609730,"text":"you might think Michelangelo\nis making fun of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612693,"text":"But he's about to dispel the gloom"},{"time":614760,"text":"by using those bright colors\nright underneath Noah:"},{"time":618302,"text":"emerald, topaz, scarlet\non the prophet Zechariah."},{"time":621716,"text":"Zechariah foresees a light\ncoming from the east,"},{"time":624719,"text":"and we are turned at this juncture\nto a new destination,"},{"time":628431,"text":"with sibyls and prophets\nwho will lead us on a parade."},{"time":632330,"text":"You have the heroes and heroines\nwho make safe the way,"},{"time":635652,"text":"and we follow the mothers and fathers."},{"time":638160,"text":"They are the motors of this great\nhuman engine, driving it forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642269,"text":"And now we're at the keystone\nof the ceiling,"},{"time":645200,"text":"the culmination of the whole thing,"},{"time":647403,"text":"with a figure that looks like\nhe's about to fall out of his space"},{"time":650657,"text":"into our space,"},{"time":652021,"text":"encroaching our space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":653328,"text":"This is the most important juncture."},{"time":655893,"text":"Past meets present."},{"time":657789,"text":"This figure, Jonah, who spent\nthree days in the belly of the whale,"},{"time":661029,"text":"for the Christians, is the symbol\nof the renewal of humanity"},{"time":663906,"text":"through Jesus' sacrifice,"},{"time":665193,"text":"but for the multitudes\nof visitors to that museum"},{"time":667965,"text":"from all faiths who visit there every day,"},{"time":670759,"text":"he is the moment the distant past\nencounters and meets immediate reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678091,"text":"All of this brings us to the yawning\narchway of the altar wall,"},{"time":682708,"text":"where we see Michelangelo's Last Judgment,"},{"time":685495,"text":"painted in 1534 after the world\nhad changed again."},{"time":689385,"text":"The Reformation had splintered the Church,"},{"time":691433,"text":"the Ottoman Empire had made\nIslam a household word"},{"time":694325,"text":"and Magellan had found a route\ninto the Pacific Ocean."},{"time":697843,"text":"How is a 59-year-old artist who has never\nbeen any further than Venice"},{"time":702529,"text":"going to speak to this new world?"},{"time":704747,"text":"Michelangelo chose to paint destiny,"},{"time":707814,"text":"that universal desire,"},{"time":709658,"text":"common to all of us,"},{"time":711302,"text":"to leave a legacy of excellence."},{"time":714495,"text":"Told in terms of the Christian vision\nof the Last Judgment,"},{"time":717450,"text":"the end of the world,"},{"time":718786,"text":"Michelangelo gave you a series of figures"},{"time":721948,"text":"who are wearing these\nstrikingly beautiful bodies."},{"time":725127,"text":"They have no more covers,\nno more portraits"},{"time":727873,"text":"except for a couple."},{"time":729134,"text":"It's a composition only out of bodies,"},{"time":731876,"text":"391, no two alike,"},{"time":735286,"text":"unique like each and every one of us."},{"time":737764,"text":"They start in the lower corner,\nbreaking away from the ground,"},{"time":741530,"text":"struggling and trying to rise."},{"time":744276,"text":"Those who have risen\nreach back to help others,"},{"time":746756,"text":"and in one amazing vignette,"},{"time":748617,"text":"you have a black man and a white man\npulled up together"},{"time":751733,"text":"in an incredible vision of human unity"},{"time":754479,"text":"in this new world."},{"time":755945,"text":"The lion's share of the space\ngoes to the winner's circle."},{"time":759476,"text":"There you find men and women\ncompletely nude like athletes."},{"time":764336,"text":"They are the ones\nwho have overcome adversity,"},{"time":766672,"text":"and Michelangelo's vision\nof people who combat adversity,"},{"time":770410,"text":"overcome obstacles --"},{"time":771708,"text":"they're just like athletes."},{"time":773626,"text":"So you have men and women\nflexing and posing"},{"time":777079,"text":"in this extraordinary spotlight."},{"time":779555,"text":"Presiding over this assembly is Jesus,"},{"time":782124,"text":"first a suffering man on the cross,"},{"time":784166,"text":"now a glorious ruler in Heaven."},{"time":786594,"text":"And as Michelangelo\nproved in his painting,"},{"time":789636,"text":"hardship, setbacks and obstacles,"},{"time":792238,"text":"they don't limit excellence,\nthey forge it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796276,"text":"Now, this does lead us to one odd thing."},{"time":798888,"text":"This is the Pope's private chapel,"},{"time":800729,"text":"and the best way you can describe that\nis indeed a stew of nudes."},{"time":803910,"text":"But Michelangelo was trying to use\nonly the best artistic language,"},{"time":807697,"text":"the most universal artistic language\nhe could think of:"},{"time":810309,"text":"that of the human body."},{"time":812093,"text":"And so instead of the way of showing\nvirtue such as fortitude or self-mastery,"},{"time":817923,"text":"he borrowed from Julius II's\nwonderful collection of sculptures"},{"time":822212,"text":"in order to show inner strength\nas external power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827368,"text":"Now, one contemporary did write"},{"time":830757,"text":"that the chapel was too beautiful\nto not cause controversy."},{"time":834639,"text":"And so it did."},{"time":836012,"text":"Michelangelo soon found\nthat thanks to the printing press,"},{"time":839574,"text":"complaints about the nudity\nspread all over the place,"},{"time":842720,"text":"and soon his masterpiece of human drama\nwas labeled pornography,"},{"time":847040,"text":"at which point he added\ntwo more portraits,"},{"time":849239,"text":"one of the man who criticized him,\na papal courtier,"},{"time":851747,"text":"and the other one of himself\nas a dried up husk, no athlete,"},{"time":855903,"text":"in the hands of a long-suffering martyr."},{"time":858348,"text":"The year he died he saw\nseveral of these figures covered over,"},{"time":862040,"text":"a triumph for trivial distractions\nover his great exhortation to glory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":868167,"text":"And so now we stand"},{"time":869955,"text":"in the here and now."},{"time":871709,"text":"We are caught in that space"},{"time":874053,"text":"between beginnings and endings,"},{"time":876342,"text":"in the great, huge totality\nof the human experience."},{"time":880598,"text":"The Sistine Chapel forces us\nto look around as if it were a mirror."},{"time":884593,"text":"Who am I in this picture?"},{"time":885914,"text":"Am I one of the crowd?"},{"time":887244,"text":"Am I the drunk guy?"},{"time":888641,"text":"Am I the athlete?"},{"time":890121,"text":"And as we leave this haven\nof uplifting beauty,"},{"time":892405,"text":"we are inspired to ask ourselves\nlife's biggest questions:"},{"time":896373,"text":"Who am I, and what role do I play\nin this great theater of life?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":901549,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902744,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":906216,"text":"Bruno Giussani: Elizabeth Lev, thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":909211,"text":"Elizabeth, you mentioned\nthis whole issue of pornography,"},{"time":913091,"text":"too many nudes and too many\ndaily life scenes and improper things"},{"time":918555,"text":"in the eyes of the time."},{"time":920444,"text":"But actually the story is bigger."},{"time":922074,"text":"It's not just touching up\nand covering up some of the figures."},{"time":925118,"text":"This work of art was almost\ndestroyed because of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928383,"text":"Elizabeth Lev: The effect\nof the Last Judgment was enormous."},{"time":931432,"text":"The printing press made sure\nthat everybody saw it."},{"time":934406,"text":"And so, this wasn't something\nthat happened within a couple of weeks."},{"time":937715,"text":"It was something that happened\nover the space of 20 years"},{"time":942207,"text":"of editorials and complaints,"},{"time":944155,"text":"saying to the Church,"},{"time":945347,"text":"\"You can't possibly tell us\nhow to live our lives."},{"time":947946,"text":"Did you notice you have\npornography in the Pope's chapel?\""},{"time":951310,"text":"And so after complaints and insistence"},{"time":953794,"text":"of trying to get this work destroyed,"},{"time":956534,"text":"it was finally the year\nthat Michelangelo died"},{"time":958719,"text":"that the Church finally\nfound a compromise,"},{"time":960824,"text":"a way to save the painting,"},{"time":962379,"text":"and that was in putting up\nthese extra 30 covers,"},{"time":965720,"text":"and that happens to be\nthe origin of fig-leafing."},{"time":968491,"text":"That's where it all came about,"},{"time":970103,"text":"and it came about from a church\nthat was trying to save a work of art,"},{"time":974257,"text":"not indeed deface or destroyed it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":976888,"text":"BG: This, what you just gave us,\nis not the classic tour"},{"time":979699,"text":"that people get today\nwhen they go to the Sistine Chapel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982697,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":984824,"text":"EL: I don't know, is that an ad?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":986629,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":988330,"text":"BG: No, no, no, not necessarily,\nit is a statement."},{"time":991342,"text":"The experience of art today\nis encountering problems."},{"time":995280,"text":"Too many people want to see this there,"},{"time":998179,"text":"and the result is five million people\ngoing through that tiny door"},{"time":1001330,"text":"and experiencing it\nin a completely different way"},{"time":1003671,"text":"than we just did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004861,"text":"EL: Right. I agree. I think it's really\nnice to be able to pause and look."},{"time":1008414,"text":"But also realize,\neven when you're in those days,"},{"time":1010739,"text":"with 28,000 people a day,"},{"time":1012775,"text":"even those days when you're in there\nwith all those other people,"},{"time":1015909,"text":"look around you and think\nhow amazing it is"},{"time":1018338,"text":"that some painted plaster\nfrom 500 years ago"},{"time":1021958,"text":"can still draw all those people\nstanding side by side with you,"},{"time":1025090,"text":"looking upwards with their jaws dropped."},{"time":1027089,"text":"It's a great statement about how beauty\ntruly can speak to us all"},{"time":1032038,"text":"through time and through geographic space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034749,"text":"BG: Liz, grazie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1035967,"text":"EL: Grazie a te."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1037198,"text":"BG: Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1038398,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}